# Excalidraw Data
## Text Elements
- Too much firing; glutamate NMDA receptors let calcium into cell (10,000x more 
    calcium on outside than inside)
- High enough level of calcium in cell triggers self destruct aka apoptosis (apoptosis is 
    important and normal, allows for gaps like separation between fingers)
- Theorized that apoptosis is what triggers slower cell death from stroke–trying to 
    target NMDA for post-stroke, saving neurons in penumbra
- Calcium can also get into cell at axon terminal (voltage gated channels)

 ^UcvzEApn

Can be triggered by hemm stroke, seizures as well ^V89yg6UJ
